I don't know of such a lemma in Mathlib, and I can't verify one exists without fabricating a citation. The closure of a compact set in a Hausdorff space is just the compact set itself (compact sets are closed in Hausdorff spaces), so a lemma phrased this way would be unusual. If you're looking for related results, Mathlib has `IsCompact.isClosed` (in `Mathlib/Topology/Separation/Basic.lean`) for the Hausdorff-implies-compact-is-closed fact, and various `PolishSpace` instances for compact metrizable spaces in `Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Polish.lean`, but I can't point to a single lemma matching your exact description. Could you share where you encountered this reference so I can search more precisely?
